dmission Controllers
- Intercept API server requests AFTER authN/authZ, BEFORE persistence.
- Types:
  1. MutatingAdmissionWebhook -> can mutate resources
  2. ValidatingAdmissionWebhook -> can validate/enforce policies
- Enabled by default (common ones):
  - NamespaceLifecycle
  - LimitRanger
  - ServiceAccount
  - ResourceQuota
- NOT enabled by default:
  - MutatingAdmissionWebhook
  - ValidatingAdmissionWebhook
  - PodSecurity (sometimes, depending on version)
- To enable webhooks: add to kube-apiserver --enable-admission-plugins flag

